Prefer libxml2's strdup and strchr

(Working around a puzzling segfault when using libc strdup on a C string
from Ruby.)

Added dependency badge for README file;

Hi,

i added VersionEye's dependency badge into README file. This badge helps to keep eye on dependencies and users will get useful metadata about your library.

Plug memory leak in XML::Text.new

XML text nodes were not being registered and never got freed and the following will eat up all memory:

  loop {
      doc = Nokogiri.XML "<r></r>"
      Nokogiri::XML::Text.new('hello', doc)
  }
